# Keep URL rewriting off for this folder so the site's pretty-URL rewrite
# rules (inherited from the parent .htaccess) never touch webhook.php.
RewriteEngine Off

# NOTE on the firewall (ModSecurity):
# Telegram delivers updates by POSTing JSON to webhook.php from its own server
# IPs. Bluehost's ModSecurity was rejecting those POSTs (409 Conflict), which
# made the bot go silent. We tried disabling ModSecurity from here with
# "SecRuleEngine Off", but this host does NOT allow that directive inside
# .htaccess and returned a 500 Internal Server Error for the whole folder.
# So ModSecurity must be turned off for this site via cPanel instead:
#   cPanel  ->  Security  ->  ModSecurity  ->  set habeshalist.com to Off (Disable)
# (or ask Bluehost support to whitelist Telegram's ranges 149.154.160.0/20 and
# 91.108.4.0/22 for /bot/ if you prefer to keep ModSecurity on for the site.)
